          "type": "link"
        }
      ],
      "name": "Millindemalion",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png",
            "name": "Related Creatures",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Similar Fey",
          "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
          "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 222",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 222",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 222,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Millindemalion practice a cruel form of hat-making, but there have been sightings of similar trickster fey who can craft shoes that never stop dancing or jackets that inflict wild mood swings onto their victims.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 222",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 222",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 222,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Millindemalions are cruel fey tricksters capable of causing mayhem with their magical, mind-altering hats. Many folktales from around the world speak of industrious fey who help struggling artisans\u2014cobblers, milliners, tailors, and so on\u2014during the night, creating quality wares in secret for no payment greater than a crumb of bread or a saucer of cream. These stories hold a grain of truth, as gracious fey do occasionally journey from the First World to aid a humble artisan on a whim, for bribes of food, or sometimes even as part of a concerted effort to spread beauty throughout the world. However, when an artisan becomes too reliant on this help, their friendly fey helper might become warped and twisted with resentment and neglect. Eventually, they could transform into a cruel prankster who delights in punishing mortals who dare task a fey with such mundane work. A millindemalion is the result of a kindly, hat-making fey undergoing such a transformation. Some scholars believe this erratic behavior is caused by the preponderance of quicksilver used in most millinery.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
